@startuml ambient_lighting_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Ambient Lighting Signal Flow\n(Input_Console / CGW -> BCM -> ambient output / IVI)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Ambient" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "CGW\nselected alert gate" as CGW #FFF4CC
participant "BCM\nambient owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "Ambient lighting\nbody output surface" as Ambient #FCE8FF
participant "IVI\nrender consumer" as IVI #E8F0FE

== Manual Ambient Input ==

Driver -> Panel : Select ambient mode
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::ambientModeCmd\nrange 0..7
note right of Panel
Input seam:
- Cmd::ambientModeCmd
- used only when scenarioActiveId == 0
end note
deactivate Panel

== Alert Context Feed ==

activate CGW
CGW -> BCM : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveLevel
CGW -> BCM : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveType
CGW -> BCM : Core::timeoutClear
note right of CGW
Auto mode uses gated alert state,
not raw donor input.
end note
deactivate CGW

== BCM Ambient Ownership ==

activate BCM
Panel -> BCM : Cmd::ambientModeCmd (manual mode)
BCM -> BCM : if scenarioActiveId == 0 -> use Cmd::ambientModeCmd
BCM -> BCM : else deriveAmbientMode(alertLevel, alertType, timeoutClear)
BCM -> BCM : deriveAmbientColorFromMode() / deriveAmbientPatternFromMode()
BCM -> Ambient : frmAmbientControlMsg\nAmbientMode / AmbientColor / AmbientPattern
BCM -> Ambient : Body::ambientMode / Body::ambientColor / Body::ambientPattern
deactivate BCM

== Downstream Visual Consumer ==

activate IVI
BCM -> IVI : Body::ambientMode
IVI -> IVI : renderMode = clamp(Body::ambientMode, 0..7)
note right of IVI
IVI consumes ambient mode as a
display/render context, while BCM
remains the real owner.
end note
deactivate IVI

Driver <- Ambient : cabin color / pattern update

note over Driver, IVI
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console can request Cmd::ambientModeCmd in manual mode
2. CGW provides the gated alert context for automatic mode
3. BCM decides the final ambient mode / color / pattern
4. BCM publishes frmAmbientControlMsg and Body::* readback
5. Ambient hardware and IVI both reflect the BCM-owned result
end note

@enduml
